name: Mountaineer Field House Refuge Restroom

Before entering the field house and indoor track space, turn left, heading down a hallway. The refuge restroom is the first door on the left, directly next to the water fountain.
comment: The Mountaineer Field House is a patron-use facility, meaning that all users must have a valid membership to utilize the facility's amenities. That said, we will never deny an individual access should they have need of a restroom.

name: Unitarian Universalist Church of Tarpon Springs
Unitarian Universalist Church of Cheyenne
directions: Go to the right when you enter the building to find the restrooms on the right before the administrative offices. Men's multistall restroom, then a large gender neutral bathroom with changing table and supplies, then women's multistall. The ramp for people with mobility needs is immediately to the left of the stairs and take the right turn to get to the admin wing, bathrooms, and nursery.
comment: The UU church is trans and queer affirming and a safe space regardless of which gender you identify with and which bathroom you wish to use. The space is open 10am-1pm on Mondays to Thursdays and in the evenings when other activities are going on. The congregation expects that visitors will be mindful of their impact and use the bathroom in a manner that makes it easy for our volunteers to maintain supplies and clean up after you (i.e. you're welcome to use one diaper to change your baby if you didn't bring one... do not make it difficult for other parents to share resources by taking a STACK of diapers or a whole bunch of menstrual supplies from the restroom without asking. If you need additional supplies or assistance, talk to the minister instead to get connected to appropriate resources and support.).
